CASA also said it would look at the announcement, but stressed that restrictions on the use of electronic devices during critical flight phases in Australia still apply.
"CASA currently has no specific regulations regarding the use of electronic devices on aircraft," it said.
The issue is subject to regulations requiring airlines to maintain safety at all times and passengers to follow safety instructions given by cabin crew.
Virgin has already held talks with CASA about extending the use of its Wi-Fi entertainment system on flights, saying it is open to change, but that it must initiate it by lawmakers.
