Syria has destroyed key facilities for the production of chemical weapons and gas munitions, the Global Chemical Weapons Monitoring Group said on Thursday, while heavy clashes broke out in the north of the country near one of the sites where suspected toxic substances are stored.
Also on Thursday, a Syrian activist group announced that more than 120,000 people had been killed since the civil war began almost three years ago.
The announcement by the Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) came one day before the deadline on
