The citizens of Pfullendorf have to be prepared for higher electricity costs.
As the managing director of Stadtwerke, Jörg-Arne Bias, confirmed to the SÜDKURIER, a family of four in Pfullendorf incurs 70 to 90 euros in additional costs per year.
The main reason for the upcoming price increase is the increase in the so-called EEG surcharge from 5.277 to 6.3 cents per kilowatt hour.
This levy is set every year in October by the four operators of the major power lines.
These quantify the additional costs incurred by them from the energy transition, which they can levy through a levy on the electricity price.
Stadtwerke Pfullendorf is the last link in this chain.
In its forecasts, the supervisory board of the energy company had even assumed a higher levy, as Jörg-Arne Bias reports.
